# Approach
if there is x ways of climbing n-2 stairs and y ways of climbing n-1 stairs, we can say that there are x+y ways of climbing n stairs. we can take 1 step from (n-1)th stair or 2 steps from (n-2)th stair to get to the nth stair.

So ans(n) = ans(n-1)+ans(n-2) i.e. Fibonacci situation.

Now we have to calculate for n>=3 only so n=1 and n=2 are already solved cases.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
O(n)


# Code
