Approach 1:- ***Recursion***
TC:- ***Exponential (2^n)***
```
class Solution:
    def climbStairs(self, n: int) -> int:
        def stairs(i):
            if i==0:
                return 1
            if i<0:
                return 0

            wayone=stairs(i-1)
            waytwo=stairs(i-2)

            return wayone+waytwo


        return stairs(n)
```
Approach 2:- ***Recursion+Memoization(Top Down DP)***
TC:- ***O(N)*** but space complexity will still have ***stack space*** involved along with ***O(N) Dp array***.

```

class Solution:
    def climbStairs(self, n: int) -> int:
        def stairs(i,dp):
            if i==0:
                return 1
            if i<0:
                return 0

            if dp[i]!=-1:
                return dp[i]

            wayone=stairs(i-1,dp)
            waytwo=stairs(i-2,dp)

            dp[i]= wayone+waytwo

            return dp[i]

        dp=[-1]*(n+1)
        return stairs(n,dp)
```
Approach 3:- ***Bottom Up DP*** 
TC:- ***O(N)*** with ***no stack space*** involved but with a **O(n)  dp array**.

```
class Solution:
    def climbStairs(self, n: int) -> int:
        def stairs(n,dp):
            for i in range(2,n+1):
                dp[i]=dp[i-1]+dp[i-2]

            return dp[n]

        dp=[-1]*(n+1)
        dp[0]=1
        dp[1]=1
        return stairs(n,dp)
```
Approach 4:- ***Space Optimisation technique!!!***
TC:- ***O(N) with NO EXTRA SPACE!!!***
