**Abstract model & visualization**

<img src="https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/90e639e3-0c19-478d-acca-79c11eb77c0b_1641029846.7747073.png" width="600" height="400" border="10"/>


---

**Hint**:

Think of **fibanacci series** and **recursion**.

Climbing Stairs can be described as following:

**Method to level n** = **Method to level (n-1)** + **Method to level (n-2)**

It's the same as the one of Fibonacci series

f( n ) = f( n - 1 ) + f( n - 2 ) 

with f( 0 ) = 1 and f( 1 ) = 1

---

```
# Base case, aka stop condition:

dp(0) = 1
dp(1) = 1
```

---

```
# General cases:

dp(n) = dp( n-1 ) + dp( n-2 ) for n >= 2
```

