A minimum of two rand7() is needed to get numbers between 1-10;

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Consider a 1 based indexed 7x7 matrix. Develop a relationship between the position and the (x,y) coordinates of the matrix. For eg. 3,5 is at the 19th position, 7,7 will be at the 49th position. 

For equal probablity of getting 1-10, some elements need to be discarded. In this case, 41-49 is discadred as it gives numbers between only 1-9.(We need 1-10,hence, unequal probability.)

Modulo operation to get the desired range of numbers(1-10).

