### **Approach :**
**Function Name :** ```inorder( TreeNode* root, set<int> &s) ```
**Return type :** ```void```

- Passing **set** as a refrence to the **inorder traversal** and store all node values into the **set**.
- Erase the ```1st smallest``` value from the set. ```s.erase(s.begin())``` .
- Then check the size of the set if size ```<1``` then ```return -1``` else ```return *s.begin()``` . 
- **Note :** ```s.begin()``` returns the **pointer** but we need **value stored** at that pointer so we ```return *s.begin()``` .

**If you like and understood the solution then don't forget to upvote solution .**

### **Solution :**

```C++
class Solution {
public:
    void inorder(TreeNode* root,set<int> &s){
        if(root==NULL) return;
        inorder(root->left,s);
        s.insert(root->val);
        inorder(root->right,s);
    }

    int findSecondMinimumValue(TreeNode* root) {
        set<int> s;
        inorder(root,s);
        s.erase(s.begin());
        return (s.size()<1)? -1:*s.begin();
    }
};
```

