solutions.content:
steps:
1. Use BFS to collect all values in the tree starting from root.
2. Use QuickSelect to quickly find the k-th smallest (or largest) element in an *un*sorted list. In this case we are quick selecting for 2nd smallest, which is k = 1.

Time:
O(n) to collect all values with BFS, O(n) quick select. T(n) = T(n/2) + O(n)

```
class Solution:
    def findSecondMinimumValue(self, root: Optional[TreeNode]) -> int:
        if not root:
            return -1

        vals = set()
        queue = collections.deque([root])
        while queue:
            curr = queue.popleft()
            if not curr:
                continue
            vals.add(curr.val)
            queue.append(curr.left)
            queue.append(curr.right)

        vals = list(vals)
        if len(vals) < 2:
            return -1
        return self.quickselect(vals, 0, len(vals) - 1, 1)


    def quickselect(self, arr, start, end, k):
        if start >= end:
            return arr[k]

        left = start
        right = end
        pivot = arr[(left + right) // 2]
        while left <= right:
            while left <= right and arr[left] < pivot:
                left += 1
            while left <= right and arr[right] > pivot:
                right -= 1
            if left <= right:
                arr[left], arr[right] = arr[right], arr[left]
                left += 1
                right -= 1
        if k <= right:
            return self.quickselect(arr, start, right, k)
        if k >= left:
            return self.quickselect(arr, left, end, k)
        return arr[k]
```

