# Approach
Firstly, I created an array of chars with 256 length.
Secondly, using for-loop I:
- Placed each character of the string on the chracter's ASCII code position, so 'A' would have index equal to 65, 'B' would have index 66 etc.
- With every letter at its own position I increased number at that position using '++'. Thus, if 'A' would occur twice, array 'arrstones' at index 65 would have 2.
Thirdly, I used next for-loop to find frequency of every letter in the 'jewels', that is stored in 'arrstones' under the letter's ASCII code index

P.S. If you liked my solution and explanation, please, like it, I would be really grateful for it

