Simple and easy java Solution in O(n) using Set.

First traverse the Jewels and keep all the char in **set** (why? because all the char in Jewel are unique).
Why Set? (Since the Search operation of a set is O(1). Hence program runs faster.
Now traverse the Stones one by one character, if they match, increment the count for that. Finally return the count
as answer.

```
class Solution {
    public int numJewelsInStones(String jewels, String stones) {
        Set<Character> set = new HashSet<>();
        for(char k:jewels.toCharArray())
            set.add(k);
        int count = 0;
        for(char k:stones.toCharArray())
            if(set.contains(k)) 
                count ++;
        return count;
    }
}
```

